cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CV, cs.CR 

The paper deals with time series classification and interpretability, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning community. The use of an opaque classifier and the focus on finding the minimum number of changes to a time series suggest that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of algorithms and optimizations also suggests that the paper could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of shapelet forests and nearest neighbor classifiers suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as these are commonly used in these fields.
